<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1988</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Saloniki</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Horton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Saloniki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-30">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 1, 5.13 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>It is officially announced that at midnight a military convention was
                                signed between commander-in-chief Allied armies here and
                                representatives Bulgarian Government. Convention brings hostilities
                                with Bulgaria to end. Bulgarian representatives accepted all terms
                                imposed by commander-in-chief including evacuation of all occupied
                                Greek and Serbian territories and complete disarmament Bulgarian
                                Army. Does Department wish me to telegraph more complete
                                details?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horton</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>